The paper deals with the use of deep neural networks for urban scene segmentation from high-resolution SAR data. This falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) category, which is the most likely category. The use of deep neural networks also suggests that the paper could belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) categories. The paper also involves the use of SAR data, which is related to the graphics (cs.GR) category. Finally, the paper discusses the use of multiple flights and antennas, which suggests that it could also belong to the robotics (cs.RO) category.
